      <akn:section eId="sec_38_356">
        <akn:num>38-356</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Complaint resolution services.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_38-356_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>The Office of Ombudsman shall provide complaint resolution services, which shall be available to current and prospective public school students and their parents or guardians.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_38-356_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>Participation in complaint resolution services provided by the Office of Ombudsman shall be voluntary.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_38-356_c">
      <akn:num>(c)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>Before submitting a complaint to the Office of Ombudsman, the complainant shall make reasonable efforts to resolve the issue at the school level.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_38-356_d">
      <akn:num>(d)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>Complainants may submit complaints by phone, in writing, or electronically.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_38-356_e">
      <akn:num>(e)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>The Office of Ombudsman shall review and investigate each complaint and shall do one or more of the following:</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
